ABOUT:
Narrow Brown Spot is caused by the fungal pathogen Cercospora oryzae. It attacks leaves at all growth stages.

SYMPTOMS:
Narrow brown streaks on leaves
Long reddish-brown lesions
Leaf drying under severe stress
Reduced photosynthesis

PREVENTION:
Apply potash fertilizers to strengthen plants
Use disease-free seeds
Improve field ventilation
Apply recommended fungicides during spread
